<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="14Jul1932"><font color="red">14 July 1932</font> <i>NLPL</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to JJ): Holroyd Reece &hellip; Reddish whiskers, a tie tied twice around a very open collar, a very clean shaven face, a talk implying &ldquo;I am the important person in this house&rdquo; &hellip; (silence is golden and speech is merely silver) &hellip; He said the power behind the scenes of the Albatross was Sir Edmund Davis (the south-african copper magnate) &hellip; However the Director of Public Prosecution &hellip; was at the mercy of receiving a letter from Mrs Grundy saying that her daughter after reading Ulysses could not see during the night nothing but spears perforating her navel and during the day other things perforating something that would be lower (this is copyrighted by me). </div>
